1. Start
2. Input the item to be added and its quantity
3. Check if the input is valid (e.g. the quantity is a positive integer)
4. If the input is invalid, display an error message and go back to step 2
5. Check if the item already exists in the inventory
6. If it does, add the quantity to the existing quantity of the item
7. If it doesn't, add the item and its quantity to the inventory
8. Display a message confirming that the item has been added to the inventory
9. Display the updated inventory
10. End
Adding inventory
// Initialize the inventory
inventory = []

// Define a function to add items to the inventory
function add_item(name, quantity):
    // Check if the item already exists in the inventory
    for item in inventory:
        if item.name == name:
            // If it does, update the quantity
            item.quantity += quantity
            return
    // If it doesn't, add the item to the inventory
    inventory.append({name: name, quantity: quantity})


